The bill does not make possession of ivory illegal and there are exceptions for the sale of common antiques pieces containi<span class="text_exposed_show">ng small amounts of ivory, such as musical instruments, guns and knives. However, it is still another big step in the right direction as state by state ivory bans continue to sweep the USA.</span>

